<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" >Grouping Tutorial
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph   >This sample exhibits the important features of the essential  grouping, and you will be guided through the following supports such as filtering , sorting, etc via Grouping engine.
</Paragraph> 

<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images\sample.png" Height="520" Width="750" /></Paragraph>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold"  >Features
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph  >It is highly optimized and can handle large amounts of dynamic data. It features support for related data and filters. All aspects of the grouping engine are extensible, and it allows users to add functionalities as needed.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph  FontWeight="Bold"  >Interactive Features
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph ><Bold> Sort on B using Default Sort </Bold> - Clicking on this button will rearrange the dynamic data in  the B coloumn with default sort. 
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph   ><Bold> Filter </Bold> - Clicking on this button will filter the dynamic data by matching with the condition in the textbox shown below the filter button.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph   ><Bold> Summary </Bold> - Clicking on this button will get the summary of the particular column selected in the column dropdown shown below. The summary display value can be customized from the summary customization dropdown.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph   ><Bold> Clear </Bold> - Customization done on the dynamic data can be cleared by clicking the respective clear options.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph  ><Bold> Reset raw data </Bold> - Clicking on this button will restore the raw data.
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph  ><Bold> Iterate </Bold> - Iterate option will help to traverse through the customized elements/records/filtered records.
</Paragraph>


